  "text": "where k is an estimate of the true mixture number k \u00c3 , and \u00c2 \u00c2 \u00bc f j ; j g k j\u00bc1 . Hereinafter, we suppose that p\u00f0xj\u00c2 \u00c2\u00de is an identifiable density with respect to \u00c2 \u00c2, i.e., for any two possible values of \u00c2 \u00c2, denoted as \u00c2 \u00c2 1 and \u00c2 \u00c2 2 , p\u00f0xj\u00c2 \u00c2 1 \u00de \u00bc p\u00f0xj\u00c2 \u00c2 2 \u00de if and only if \u00c2 \u00c2 1 \u00bc \u00c2 \u00c2 2 . In general, after preassigning the value of k, the learning of \u00c2 \u00c2 can be achieved via the EM algorithm [CITATION_1] ",
